  "41 - Hydraulic circuit test": {
   "width": 15420,
   "height": 11580,
   "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
   "labels": [
    {
     "text": "Routine status",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "2",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 10440,
      "top": 5520,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 2160
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 10.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "Hydraulic circuit test routine",
     "color": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "alignment": "2",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": -360,
      "top": 0,
      "height": 600,
      "width": 15720
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 16.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "1. Engine stopped, if the brake pedal run is large ==> Some air is present in the primary hydraulic braking circuit.",
     "color": "rgb(255,128,128)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(64,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 0,
      "top": 600,
      "height": 840,
      "width": 15480
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "==> DO NOT CHECK the hydraulic circuit BUT make a hydraulic circuit BLEED.",
     "color": "rgb(255,128,128)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(64,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 0,
      "top": 1440,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 15480
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "2. To test the hydraulic braking circuit, stop the engine and push three times on the braking pedal.",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 0,
      "top": 1800,
      "height": 240,
      "width": 11040
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "==> If the braking pedal may still run, then, air is present in the primary hydraulic braking circuit.",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 480,
      "top": 2085,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 10920
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "==> Else, the braking circuit is OK",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 480,
      "top": 2400,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 10920
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
